-- Renaissance Services Gets $100 Million Financing for Offshore Operations
-- Arif Sharif
-- 2010-08-02T04:30:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-02/renaissance-services-gets-100-million-financing-for-offshore-operations.html

          
          
             Renaissance Services Co., an Omani
energy services company, obtained 38.5 million rials in
financing to expand its offshore support vessel operations.  
 Renaissance signed a syndicated term-loan facility of 19.25
million rials, arranged by Bank Dhofar and National Bank of
Oman, the company said in a statement to the Muscat bourse
today. The company will sign an accord on a 19.25 million-rial
facility with an Omani bank soon, it said.  
